object.script:
integral = 0 pvOld = 0 out = 0
max = 1 min = 0
function onTick() setpoint = input.getNumber(1) pv = input.getNumber(2) P = input.getNumber(3) I = input.getNumber(4) D = input.getNumber(5)
on = input.getBool(1)
if on then error = setpoint - pv diff = pv - pvOld
if out < max and out > min then integral = integral + I*error integral = math.max(math.min(integral, max), min) end
Kp = P*error Ki = integral Kd = -D*diff
out = Kp+Ki+Kd out = math.max(math.min(out, max), min)
else integral = 0 out = 0 end
pvOld = pv
output.setNumber(1, out) end

object.script:
pi=math.pi tau=pi*2 cos=math.cos sin=math.sin atan=math.atan abs=math.abs sdL=screen.drawLine sdR=screen.drawRect sdRF=screen.drawRectF sdT=screen.drawText ssC=screen.setColor function sign(number) return number > 0 and 1 or (number == 0 and 0 or -1) end
function onTick() dist = property.getNumber("Distance to Monitor (Blocks)") monitor = property.getNumber("Monitor Size (Blocks)") tiltUp = input.getNumber(1) tiltLeft = input.getNumber(2) tiltForward = input.getNumber(3) lX = input.getNumber(9) lY = input.getNumber(10) roll=atan(tiltLeft,tiltUp) pitch=tiltForward*tau rollC=cos(-roll) rollS=sin(-roll) rollC2=cos(-roll+tau/4) rollS2=sin(-roll+tau/4)
brt=property.getNumber("Background Brightness (%)")/100
tr=property.getNumber("Top R")*brt tg=property.getNumber("Top G")*brt tb=property.getNumber("Top B")*brt
br=property.getNumber("Bottom R")*brt bg=property.getNumber("Bottom G")*brt bb=property.getNumber("Bottom B")*brt
pitchStep = 10 lW = 8 --overall line width lMW = 3 -- line space from center lH = 21 -- vertical line spacing ptchMult=tau*96/(pitchStep/2) --pitch multiplier, obviously brH = 4 --height of bracket part
end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() size=(h/monitor)*dist lXO = math.floor(math.tan(lX)*size) lYO = math.floor(math.tan(-lY)*size*2.5)
xpitch=-rollS*pitch*ptchMult ypitch=rollC*pitch*ptchMult bPosX=w/2+xpitch bPosY=h/2+ypitch
radius=w*4 for i=0, 360*10 do if (i/10+roll*(180/pi))%360>180 then screen.setColor(tr, tg, tb) elseif (i/10+roll*(180/pi))%360<180 then screen.setColor(br, bg, bb) end screen.drawLine(bPosX, bPosY, bPosX+cos(i/10*(pi/180))*radius, bPosY+sin(i/10*(pi/180))*radius) end
ssC(200, 200, 200) for i=-12, 12 do rPosX=w/2+lXO+rollC2*i*lH rPosY=h/2+lYO+rollS2*i*lH xrPosX=w/2+lXO+rollC2*(i*lH+5) xrPosY=h/2+lYO+rollS2*(i*lH+5) xrPosX2=w/2+lXO+rollC2*(i*lH-5) xrPosY2=h/2+lYO+rollS2*(i*lH-5)
--lmx1 = (w/2+rollC2*h/2)+rollC*(w/2)+(15)+(xpitch) --horizon line --lmy1 = (h/2+rollS2*h/2)+rollS*(w/2)+(15)+(ypitch) --lmx2 = (w/2+rollC2*h/2)+rollC*(w/2)-(15)+(xpitch) --lmy2 = (h/2+rollS2*h/2)+rollS*(w/2)-(15)+(ypitch) --screen.drawLine(lmx1, lmy1, lmx2, lmy2)
lrx1 = (rPosX)+rollC*lW+(xpitch) --right horizontal line positions lry1 = (rPosY)+rollS*lW+(ypitch) lrx2 = (rPosX)+rollC*lMW+(xpitch) lry2 = (rPosY)+rollS*lMW+(ypitch)
llx1 = (rPosX)+rollC*-lW+(xpitch) --left horizontal line positions lly1 = (rPosY)+rollS*-lW+(ypitch) llx2 = (rPosX)+rollC*-lMW+(xpitch) lly2 = (rPosY)+rollS*-lMW+(ypitch)
if abs(i)==9 then
xx1 = (xrPosX)+rollC*lW+(xpitch) xy1 = (xrPosY)+rollS*lW+(rollC*(pitch*ptchMult+5)) --cross for positive/negative90 xx2 = (xrPosX2)+rollC*-lW+(xpitch) xy2 = (xrPosY2)+rollS*-lW+(rollC*(pitch*ptchMult-5)) xx3 = (xrPosX2)+rollC*lW+(xpitch) xy3 = (xrPosY2)+rollS*lW+(rollC*(pitch*ptchMult-5)) xx4 = (xrPosX)+rollC*-lW+(xpitch) xy4 = (xrPosY)+rollS*-lW+(rollC*(pitch*ptchMult+5))
sdL(xx1, xy1, xx2, xy2) sdL(xx3, xy3, xx4, xy4)
else
if i<=0 then sdL(lrx1, lry1, lrx2, lry2) --right line sdL(llx1, lly1, llx2, lly2) --left line else
for e=0, 1 do
t1 = lMW+1+(e*4+e) t2 = lMW+3+(e*4-e)
sdL((rPosX)+rollC*t1+(xpitch), (rPosY)+rollS*t1+(ypitch), (rPosX)+rollC*t2+(xpitch), (rPosY)+rollS*t2+(ypitch)) -- right neg sdL((rPosX)+rollC*-t1+(xpitch), (rPosY)+rollS*-t1+(ypitch), (rPosX)+rollC*-t2+(xpitch), (rPosY)+rollS*-t2+(ypitch)) --left end end
sdL(lrx1, lry1, lrx1-rollC2*sign(i)*brH, lry1-rollS2*sign(i)*brH) --right bracket
sdL(llx1, lly1, llx1-rollC2*sign(i)*brH, lly1-rollS2*sign(i)*brH) --left bracket end
end
end

function onTick() blink = input.getBool(1) on = input.getBool(3) rng = input.getNumber(11) azi = math.tan(input.getNumber(12)*math.pi*2) elev = math.tan(input.getNumber(13)*math.pi*2) lX = input.getNumber(9) lY = input.getNumber(10) dist = property.getNumber("Distance to Monitor (Blocks)") monitor = property.getNumber("Monitor Size (Blocks)") offset = property.getNumber("Radar Vertical Offset (Degrees)")*(math.pi/180) --rDistz = property.getNumber("Vertical Distance from Radar to HUD (Blocks)") --rDistx = property.getNumber("Horizontal Distance from Radar to HUD (Blocks)") rectsize = property.getNumber("Radar Target Indicator Square Size (Pixels)") fovX = property.getNumber("Targeting Radar Horizontal FOV")*math.pi*2 fovY = property.getNumber("Targeting Radar Vertical FOV")*math.pi*2 function clamp(x,a,b) return x<a and a or x>b and b or x end
end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
--offset=math.tan(rDistz/rDistx)/(math.pi*2) size=(h/monitor)*dist lXOffset = math.floor(math.tan(lX)*size) lYOffset = math.floor(math.tan(-lY-offset)*size*2.5)
searchX = math.floor(math.tan(fovX)*size) searchY = math.floor(math.tan(fovY)*size)
posX=clamp(math.floor(w/2+(size*azi)+lXOffset), 0, w) posY=clamp(math.floor(h/2+(-size*elev)+lYOffset), 0, h)
if elev==0 and azi==0 then if blink and on then screen.setColor(0,255,0) screen.drawRect(w/2-searchX/2+lXOffset-1, h/2-searchY/2+lYOffset, searchX, searchY) end elseif on then screen.setColor(0, 0, 0, 220) screen.drawRectF(0, 0, w, h)
screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawRect(posX-rectsize/2, posY-rectsize/2, rectsize, rectsize) end end

function onTick() lX = input.getNumber(9) lY = input.getNumber(10) up = input.getNumber(21) fw = input.getNumber(22) rt = input.getNumber(23) dist = property.getNumber("Distance to Monitor (Blocks)") monitor = property.getNumber("Monitor Size (Blocks)") velvect = property.getBool("Velocity Vector") function clamp(x,a,b) return x<a and a or x>b and b or x end
Rsize=2 end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(200, 200, 200) size=(h/monitor)*dist lXOffset = math.floor(math.tan(lX)*size) lYOffset = math.floor(math.tan(-lY)*size*2.5) posX=clamp(math.floor(w/2+(size*rt/fw)+lXOffset), 0, w) posY=clamp(math.floor(h/2+(-size*up/fw)+1+lYOffset), 0, h) oposX=clamp(math.floor(w/2+lXOffset), 0, w) oposY=clamp(math.floor(h/2+1+lYOffset), 0, h)
if velvect then if fw>5 then screen.drawRect(posX-Rsize/2, posY-Rsize/2, Rsize, Rsize) screen.drawLine(posX+2, posY, posX+4, posY) screen.drawLine(posX-2, posY, posX-4, posY) screen.drawLine(posX, posY-2, posX, posY-4) else screen.drawRect(oposX-Rsize/2, oposY-Rsize/2, Rsize, Rsize) screen.drawLine(oposX+2, oposY, oposX+4, oposY) screen.drawLine(oposX-2, oposY, oposX-4, oposY) screen.drawLine(oposX, oposY-2, oposX, oposY-4) end end end

pi=math.pi tau=pi*2 cos=math.cos sin=math.sin atan=math.atan abs=math.abs sdL=screen.drawLine sdR=screen.drawRect sdRF=screen.drawRectF sdT=screen.drawText ssC=screen.setColor function onTick() dist = property.getNumber("Distance to Monitor (Blocks)") monitor = property.getNumber("Monitor Size (Blocks)") altUnit = property.getNumber("Altitude Unit") speedUnit = property.getNumber("Speed Unit") machD = property.getBool("Mach Speed Indicator") lX = input.getNumber(9) lY = input.getNumber(10) NVD = input.getBool(2) altitude = input.getNumber(24)*altUnit speed = input.getNumber(25)*speedUnit mach = input.getNumber(25)/343 heading = input.getNumber(26)
if NVD then opaque=200 else opaque=225 end --opaque=225 end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() size=(h/monitor)*dist lXO = math.floor(math.tan(lX)*size) lYO = math.floor(math.tan(-lY)*size*2.5)
altx=w-20+lXO spdx=1+lXO hdgx=w/2-7+lXO
alty=h/2-18+lYO spdy=alty hdgy=1+lYO ssC(0, 0, 0, opaque) sdRF(altx-2, alty-2, 23, 8) --opaque rectangles sdRF(spdx-2, spdy-2, 23, 8) sdRF(hdgx-2, hdgy-2, 18, 8)
ssC(200, 200, 200) --text sdT(altx, alty, string.format("%0004.0f", altitude)) sdT(spdx, spdy, string.format("%0004.0f", abs(speed))) sdT(hdgx, hdgy, string.format("%003.0f", heading)) if machD then sdT(7+lXO, h/2+10+lYO, string.format("%1.02f", abs(mach))) end
sdR(altx-2, alty-2, 22, 8) --main rectangles sdR(spdx-2, spdy-2, 22, 8) sdR(hdgx-2, hdgy-2, 17, 8)
mow=15 miw=3 mih=4 screen.setColor(150, 150, 0) sdL(w/2-mow, h/2, w/2-miw, h/2) --horizontal middle sdL(w/2+mow, h/2, w/2+miw, h/2)
sdL(w/2-miw, h/2, w/2-miw, h/2+mih) sdL(w/2+miw, h/2, w/2+miw, h/2+mih) end

object.script:
sc,inp,out=screen,input,output freq=16 freqb=freq ptt=false
function hex2rgb(hex) hex = hex:gsub("#","") return {r=tonumber("0x"..hex:sub(1,2)), g=tonumber("0x"..hex:sub(3,4)), b=tonumber("0x"..hex:sub(5,6))} end
function onTick() p = inp.getBool(1) x = inp.getNumber(3) y = inp.getNumber(4) str = inp.getNumber(5) recv = inp.getBool(3) out.setNumber(1,freq) out.setBool(1,ptt)
BGC = hex2rgb(property.getText("Background Color (Hex)")) FGC = hex2rgb(property.getText("Foreground Color (Hex)")) end function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
sc.setColor(BGC["r"],BGC["g"],BGC["b"],255) sc.drawClear() sc.setColor(FGC["r"]*0.3,FGC["g"]*0.3,FGC["b"]*0.3,255) if y > 24 then if x < 8 and p then sc.drawRectF(0,25,8,10) if freq > 1 then freq=freqb-1 end elseif x > 8 and x < 16 and p then sc.drawRectF(9,25,8,10) if freq < 88 then freq=freqb+1 end else freqb=freq end if x > 16 and p then sc.drawRectF(16,25,16,8) ptt=true else ptt=false end end if recv then sc.setColor(FGC["r"],FGC["g"],FGC["b"],255) else sc.setColor(FGC["r"]*0.05,FGC["g"]*0.05,FGC["b"]*0.05,255) end sc.drawText(4,10,"INCOM")
sx = 19 sy = -9 sc.setColor(FGC["r"]*0.05,FGC["g"]*0.05,FGC["b"]*0.05,255) if str > 0.8 then sc.setColor(FGC["r"],FGC["g"],FGC["b"],255) end sc.drawRectF(10+sx,10+sy,1,5) if str > 0.65 then sc.setColor(FGC["r"],FGC["g"],FGC["b"],255) end sc.drawRectF(8+sx,11+sy,1,4) if str > 0.35 then sc.setColor(FGC["r"],FGC["g"],FGC["b"],255) end sc.drawRectF(6+sx,12+sy,1,3) if str > 0.1 then sc.setColor(FGC["r"],FGC["g"],FGC["b"],255) end sc.drawRectF(4+sx,13+sy,1,2)
sc.setColor(FGC["r"],FGC["g"],FGC["b"],255) sc.drawLine(0,24,w,24) sc.drawLine(0,7,w,7) sc.drawLine(8,25,8,32) sc.drawLine(16,25,16,32) sc.drawText(2,26,"<") sc.drawText(11,26,">") sc.drawText(18,26,"PTT") sc.drawText(4,17,"CH:"..string.format("%.0f",freq)) sc.drawText(2,1,"SD-C") end

object.script:
samples = {}
tick = 1 iter = 1 tickStart = 1
fuelD = 0 fuelDOld = 0 fuelA = 0 fuelAOld = 0 speedA = 0 speedAOld = 0
rate1 = 0 rate2 = 0 time = 0 range = 0
start = false
function onTick() fuel = math.max(input.getNumber(1), 0) speed = math.abs(input.getNumber(2))
sampleMax = property.getNumber("Sampling time")
if tickStart < 60 then tickStart = tickStart+1 end
if not start and tickStart >= 60 and fuel > 0 then start = true for i = 1,sampleMax do samples[i] = {} samples[i][1] = fuel samples[i][2] = 0 end fuelA = fuel fuelAOld = fuel end
if start then if tick > 60 then fuelAOld = fuelA fuelDOld = fuelD speedAOld = speedA speedA = 0 fuelA = 0
tick = 0
samples[iter][1] = fuel samples[iter][2] = speed
for i in pairs(samples) do fuelA = fuelA + samples[i][1] speedA = speedA + samples[i][2] end fuelA = fuelA/sampleMax speedA = speedA/sampleMax fuelD = fuelAOld - fuelA
iter = iter+1 if iter > sampleMax then iter = 1 end end
tick1 = tick/60 rate1 = math.max(fuelDOld*(1-tick1)+fuelD*tick1, 0) fuelALerp = math.max(fuelAOld*(1-tick1)+fuelA*tick1, 0) speedALerp = math.max(speedAOld*(1-tick1)+speedA*tick1, 0)
if rate1 > 0.001 then time = math.min(fuelALerp/(rate1*60), 1000) range = math.min(speedALerp*time*0.06, 10000) else time = 0 range = 0 end
if speed > 1 then rate2 = rate1*1000/speed else rate2 = 0 end
tick = tick+1 end
output.setNumber(1, rate1) output.setNumber(2, rate2) output.setNumber(3, math.floor(time)) output.setNumber(4, math.floor(range)) end

object.script:
function onTick() --start inputs for the triangle indicator Heading = (math.rad((input.getNumber(1)+90)%360-180))
x = input.getNumber(2) y = input.getNumber(3)
function TriangleIndicator(x1,y1,length,a,b,c)
screen.setColor(a,b,c)
xTip = (length*math.cos(Heading))+x1
yTip = (length*math.sin(Heading))+y1
xInitial = (length*math.cos(Heading+math.pi))+x1
yInitial = (length*math.sin(Heading+math.pi))+y1
xRight = (length/1.5*math.cos(Heading+math.pi/2)+xInitial)
yRight = (length/1.5*math.sin(Heading+math.pi/2)+yInitial)
xLeft = (length/1.5*math.cos(Heading-math.pi/2)+xInitial)
yLeft = (length/1.5*math.sin(Heading-math.pi/2)+yInitial)
--the 90 degree lines comin up!
screen.drawLine(xInitial,yInitial,xRight,yRight)
screen.drawLine(xInitial,yInitial,xLeft,yLeft)
screen.drawLine(xRight,yRight,xTip,yTip)
screen.drawLine(xLeft,yLeft,xTip,yTip) end
end
function onDraw() screen.drawMap(x,y,20) TriangleIndicator(32,16,3,255,124,1)
end
